<step><![CDATA[Place the sake or plum wine in a small saucepan and simmer gently over medium head until reduced by half. Combine with the lemon juice and zest, vinegar, and olive oil and whisk to combine.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Meanwhile, place the hazelnuts in a dry frying pan over low-medium heat and toast, shaking the pan occasionally for 4-5 minutes or until fragrant and nutty smelling.]]></step>
</directions>
